### =====================================================
### Variables
### =====================================================
@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080
@keycloakUrl = http://localhost:8180
@realm = endurance
@clientId = backend
@clientSecret = Hvkh9JcoLjjNFT8FIgd3qPpJZWT3E7v9
@usernameVeteran = Mathias
@usernameSupport = Lee
@password = password

### =====================================================
### 1. Get access token – VETERAN
### =====================================================
POST {{keycloakUrl}}/realms/{{realm}}/protocol/openid-connect/token
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

grant_type = password &
client_id = {{clientId}} &
client_secret = {{clientSecret}} &
username = {{usernameVeteran}} &
password = {{password}} &
scope = openid

> {%
    client.global.set("veteranToken", response.body.access_token);
%}

### =====================================================
### 2. Get access token – SUPPORT
### =====================================================
POST {{keycloakUrl}}/realms/{{realm}}/protocol/openid-connect/token
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

grant_type = password &
client_id = {{clientId}} &
client_secret = {{clientSecret}} &
username = {{usernameSupport}} &
password = {{password}} &
scope = openid

> {%
    client.global.set("supportToken", response.body.access_token);
%}

### =====================================================
### 3. Ensure users exist in DB
### =====================================================

### 3a. Get or create VETERAN
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/me
Authorization: Bearer {{veteranToken}}

### 3b. Get or create SUPPORT
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/me
Authorization: Bearer {{supportToken}}

### =====================================================
### Mood – Happy paths
### =====================================================

### 4. Submit mood entry for today (with notes)
POST {{baseUrl}}/mood/entries
Authorization: Bearer {{veteranToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "date": "2026-02-26",
  "moodScore": 7,
  "notes": "Feeling pretty good today, went for a walk."
}

### 5. Submit mood entry for today without notes
POST {{baseUrl}}/mood/entries
Authorization: Bearer {{veteranToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "date": "2026-02-26",
  "moodScore": 5
}

### 6. Submit a second mood entry for the same day – both are stored
POST {{baseUrl}}/mood/entries
Authorization: Bearer {{veteranToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "date": "2026-02-26",
  "moodScore": 9,
  "notes": "Actually had a great day!"
}

### 7. Submit mood entry for a different day
POST {{baseUrl}}/mood/entries
Authorization: Bearer {{veteranToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "date": "2026-02-25",
  "moodScore": 3,
  "notes": "Yesterday was tough."
}

### 8. Submit mood entry with minimum score (1)
POST {{baseUrl}}/mood/entries
Authorization: Bearer {{veteranToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "date": "2026-02-24",
  "moodScore": 1
}

### 9. Submit mood entry with maximum score (10)
POST {{baseUrl}}/mood/entries
Authorization: Bearer {{veteranToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "date": "2026-02-23",
  "moodScore": 10,
  "notes": "Best day ever."
}

### =====================================================
### Mood – Error / constraint paths
### =====================================================

### 10. No auth token → expect 401
POST {{baseUrl}}/mood/entries
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "date": "2026-02-26",
  "moodScore": 7
}

### 11. moodScore below range (0) → expect 422
POST {{baseUrl}}/mood/entries
Authorization: Bearer {{veteranToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "date": "2026-02-26",
  "moodScore": 0
}

### 12. moodScore above range (11) → expect 422
POST {{baseUrl}}/mood/entries
Authorization: Bearer {{veteranToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "date": "2026-02-26",
  "moodScore": 11
}

### 13. Missing moodScore → expect 422
POST {{baseUrl}}/mood/entries
Authorization: Bearer {{veteranToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "date": "2026-02-26"
}

### 14. Missing date → expect 422
POST {{baseUrl}}/mood/entries
Authorization: Bearer {{veteranToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "moodScore": 7
}

### 15. Invalid date format → expect 422
POST {{baseUrl}}/mood/entries
Authorization: Bearer {{veteranToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "date": "26-02-2026",
  "moodScore": 7
}

### 16. Notes exceeding 500 characters → expect 422
POST {{baseUrl}}/mood/entries
Authorization: Bearer {{veteranToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "date": "2026-02-26",
  "moodScore": 6,
  "notes": ""
}

### =====================================================
### Mood – Update entry (PUT)
### =====================================================

### 17. Update a mood entry – full replace (happy path)
### Replace <entry-id> with a real UUID from a previous POST response
PUT {{baseUrl}}/mood/entries/0533fed5-e44a-4ea7-94d2-8c015ee3034f
Authorization: Bearer {{veteranToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "date": "2026-02-26",
  "moodScore": 8,
  "notes": "Updated: feeling even better after reflection."
}

### 18. Update a mood entry – remove notes (omit field)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/mood/entries/0533fed5-e44a-4ea7-94d2-8c015ee3034f
Authorization: Bearer {{veteranToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "date": "2026-02-26",
  "moodScore": 6,
  "notes": "i'm feeling pretty down"
}

### 19. Update – no auth token → expect 401
PUT {{baseUrl}}/mood/entries/<entry-id>
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "date": "2026-02-26",
  "moodScore": 8
}

### 20. Update – entry does not exist → expect 404
PUT {{baseUrl}}/mood/entries/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
Authorization: Bearer {{veteranToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "date": "2026-02-26",
  "moodScore": 8
}

### 21. Update – entry belongs to another user → expect 403
PUT {{baseUrl}}/mood/entries/<entry-id>
Authorization: Bearer {{supportToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "date": "2026-02-26",
  "moodScore": 8
}

### 22. Update – invalid entry ID format → expect 400
PUT {{baseUrl}}/mood/entries/not-a-uuid
Authorization: Bearer {{veteranToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "date": "2026-02-26",
  "moodScore": 8
}

### 23. Update – moodScore out of range → expect 422
PUT {{baseUrl}}/mood/entries/<entry-id>
Authorization: Bearer {{veteranToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "date": "2026-02-26",
  "moodScore": 11
}

### 24. Update – invalid date format → expect 422
PUT {{baseUrl}}/mood/entries/<entry-id>
Authorization: Bearer {{veteranToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "date": "26-02-2026",
  "moodScore": 8
}

### =====================================================
### Mood – Delete entry (DELETE)
### =====================================================

### 25. Delete a mood entry (happy path) → expect 204
### Replace <entry-id> with a real UUID from a previous POST response
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/mood/entries/0533fed5-e44a-4ea7-94d2-8c015ee3034f
Authorization: Bearer {{veteranToken}}

### 26. Delete – no auth token → expect 401
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/mood/entries/<entry-id>

### 27. Delete – entry does not exist → expect 404
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/mood/entries/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
Authorization: Bearer {{veteranToken}}

### 28. Delete – entry belongs to another user → expect 403
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/mood/entries/<entry-id>
Authorization: Bearer {{supportToken}}

### 29. Delete – invalid entry ID format → expect 400
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/mood/entries/not-a-uuid
Authorization: Bearer {{veteranToken}}
